description:
&lt;p&gt;De Cham is a 28 bedded mixed medical ward; 8 of these beds will be gastroenterology, the remaining beds can be any general medicine and of variable age.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return for your hard work and dedication, East Sussex Healthcare Trust offers excellent opportunities for career progression and professional development, as well as a personal induction programme, with opportunities for cannulation, venepuncture, TPN and PEG/RIG feeding as well as many other aspects of medical nursing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Whether you are just starting out on your Nursing career, looking for a change of job, working in a Nursing Home or even returning to practice, we would welcome the opportunity to meet with you, our team is both friendly and supportive, with a strong commitment to providing a high standard of care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will have recent nursing preferably with experience in the field of acute medical nursing. Ideally you will have, a recognised teaching and assessing qualifications, be able to work within a team and have effective communication skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The acute medical patients can present with a variety of problems, such as sepsis and substance misuse. There is constant interaction between medical and nursing staff, which cultivates a supportive environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We also work closely with the University of Brighton and offer valuable management placements for nursing students.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Su Sparkes&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Matron&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;su.sparkes@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
